7.Be2  { An important idea to remember! We want to castle artificially by playing [Rf1] and [Kg1] next. King's safety matters, especially in Rapid and Blitz! } d6  ( 7...N8e7?! { This natural developing move allows a powerful response! } 8.h4! { A slight change of our plan: it turns out the [e7]-knight blocks Black's queen and now we can develop initiative by targetting the [g6]–knight! Black has a hard time finding good squares for his knights. Bishops are much more powerful in an open position like this. White is clearly better. } ) 
