7.Nxc6 $1 { In this case, it makes sense to damage Black's pawn structure instead of going for a plan with [O-O-O] - since Black did not waste time for [d7]-[d6], he can immediately strike in the center with [d7]-[d5]! and get a comfortable position. } dxc6  { Just leads to a better endgame for White due to the pawn structure: } 
8.Qxd8  Rxd8  
9.f3 $1 { Preparing 8...-- 9.Be3 and preventing [Ng4]. A useful move in our setup in general. } Be6  
10.Ne2 $1 {[%cal Be2f4]} {[%csl Bf4]} {[%cal Bf1c4]} {[%cal Bc1e3]} {[%csl Re6]} { Another nice idea! Knight is heading to [f4] harassing Black's bishop on [e6]. We can then play [Bc4] and [Be3]. Black struggles to find good squares for his pieces. White has an edge. }  *

