8.h3  { Taking the g4-square under control and preparing Qd2. } ( { Immediate } 8.Qd2 { runs into } 8...Bg4 { . } { It is useful to delay castling - it keeps more tension in the position and forces your opponent to take into account both [O-O] and [O-O-O]! } ) ( { Again, } 8.h4?! { would not be a good idea due to } 8...Bg4! ) Be6 $5 { Trading our good bishop, but spoiling the pawn-structure a bit. } 
9.Bxe6  fxe6  
10.Ne2 $1 {[%cal Be2g3]} { The knight is heading to [g3] anticipating [d6]-[d5]. } d5  
