6.Ng5  { Improving our knight, targetting the [f7]-pawn. We have exploited Black's move [h7]-[h5] in this way. } b5 $6 { Played in the spirit of the previous move. Nevertheless, after that Black is under severe pressure: } ( 6...Nf6 { in this case we go for a common setup, starting with } 7.f3 { , solidifying of pawn-structure. We take the [g4]-square under control and want to play [Be3], [Qd2], and [O-O-O] next. } 7...O-O 8.Be3 b5 9.Qd2 { followed by } 9...-- 10.O-O-O { , } -- 11.Be2 { and eventually } 11...-- {g4 breaking through on the queenside. } ) 
