3.h4 $5 {[%cal Bh4h5]} {[%csl Rg6]} {[%cal Gh1h8]} ( 3. h4 { The main idea of our strategy. Black faces an unpleasant choice already on the 3rd move. It is not clear whether he should allow h5, play } 3...h5 { himself, or maybe play } {3...h6 with the idea to meet 4.h5 with 4...g5? In any case, we will be ready for whatever he chooses. } ) ( 3. h4 3...Nf6? { runs into } 4.e5 { and the knight has to go back to } 4...Ng8 { since } {4...Nh5 runs into 5.g4 +- } ) h6  {[%cal Bd2d4]} {[%cal Bc1e3]} {[%cal Bd1d2]} {[%csl Rh6]} {[%cal Bh4h5]} {[%cal Bg6g5]} ( 3... h6 { With the intention to play } 4.h5 g5 { . } ) ( 3... h6 { There is one important nuance to understand: after we play } 4.d4 { , } -- 5.Be3 { and } 5...-- 6.Qd2 { , the pawn on [h6] will be under attack and Black will not be able to castle. } ) 
4.d4  {[%cal Bc1e3]} {[%cal Bd1d2]} {[%cal Be1c1]} d6  
