8.d5 $5 {[%cal Ba5h5]} {[%csl Bd5]} c6  
9.b4 $1 Qd8  ( { Taking on b4, } 9...Qxb4 { allows } 10.Rb1 { , after which the [b7]-pawn falls and Black is in trouble. } ) 
10.Nf4  { Defending the [d5]-pawn. } cxd5  
11.Nfxd5  {[%cal Bc1f4]} {[%cal Bf1e1]} Nxd5  
12.Nxd5  e6  
13.Re1 $16 {[%cal Bc1f4]} {[%cal Bc1b2]} ( 13. Re1 { Pinning the e6-pawn and tactically defending our knight. We have a threat of } 13...-- 14.Bf4 { and an option of } {14.Bb2 . In a practical game, I can hardly imagine Black surviving here. } )  *

