9.Bg2  {[%cal Bg2b7]} { Improving our bishop and taking the-[e4] square under control before executing our main idea of [h4]-[h5]. Good news is that this move is attacking the [b7]-pawn and forces Black to react. } c6  
10.h4 $1 {[%cal Bh4h5]} ( 10. h4 10...-- 11.h5 { is a huge threat. } ) Bb4  
11.O-O  ( 11. O-O { Breaking the pin and threatening h4-h5 again. Black now has nothing better than allowing damage to his pawn structure by playing h7-h6, for instance: } 11...Bxc3 12.bxc3 Be4 { doesn't help because the bishop will be trapped in the middle of the board! } 13.f3 Bd5 14.c4 { +- } )  *

